-- Central Banks Can Absorb Liquidity, Hildebrand Says
-- B y   K l a u s   W i l l e
-- 2012-09-17T14:39:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-17/central-banks-can-absorb-liquidity-hildebrand-says-correct-.html
(Corrects first paragraph to show Hildebrand will join
BlackRock as vice chairman Oct. 1.)  Central banks will have “the right
instruments to absorb liquidity” and fight inflation “when the
time comes,” former Swiss central bank president Philipp
Hildebrand, who will join  BlackRock Inc. (BLK)  as vice chairman Oct.
1, said at an event in  Singapore  today.  Still, the time hasn’t come yet, Hildebrand said without
elaborating.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Klaus Wille in Zurich at 
 kwille@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
